Who Are You?
[trigger none]
[vignette intro/the_ring]

Your hand strays to your finger, still not quite used to the weight that rides there. The band sits heavy and unfamiliar against the bone. You ease it free and turn it slowly in the light, studying the ornate seal.

A signet ring, gold, weathered from years of use. This ring has stamped contracts, treaties, death sentences. It opens doors for the bearer, loosens tongues, carries the grim authority of the **Trade Guild**.

You are not the first owner. How did you come by this ring?

choices:

* Murder = I took it by force
  The fat bastard bled more than you'd expected. You still feel the spray of it when you close your eyes, still see his hand twitching in that alley muck. The Guild will gut you for this theft if they catch you, but the borderlands are a lawless place. A land of blood, gold, and shadow, and you were born for all three.
  +set_skill combat 4
  +set_skill bushcraft 2
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +set_name "The Outlaw"
  +open Gameplay_Intro

* Birthright = My mother once wore this, but it is now mine
  This was your mother's ring, and she wielded it like a hammer. Grim, dangerous men bent knee before her. You remember the smell of sea-salt in her hair, her litle rituals like turning the signet once before pressing wax to a contract. She said the ring would secure the family's future, and you mean to see that through.
  +set_skill mercantile 4
  +set_skill negotiation 4
  +set_name "The Scion"
  +open Gameplay_Intro

* Gambling = I won it in a game
  You still remember the trader's face when you called his bluff; the way his grin fell as you laid down your cards. The whole den had gone silent, eyes upon you and your impossible hand. The man had thought wagering a Guild signet would cow a room of dockside rabble, but you've always had the devil's luck. Now his ruin buys you a new life, and fortune willing, even greater rewards.
  +set_skill negotiation 2
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +set_skill luck 4
  +set_name "The Gambler"
  +open Gameplay_Intro

* A Gift = It was given to me
  The girl was nearly starved and half-mad when you found her, crouched beneath the roots of a storm-felled cedar. Her father's finest hunters gave up the search after the first week, but not you. You followed the broken language of the forest, the snapped twigs, the hush of disturbed birds, the faint drag-marks, and you found her. Later, in a hall heavy with song and gratitude, her father presented you with his ring. At home, he is the generous lord and you are a nameless hunter. But here, in this new land, you mean to write your own story.
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +set_skill bushcraft 4
  +set_skill combat 2
  +set_name "The Huntsman"
  +open Gameplay_Intro

* A Commission = The Guild sent me
  Twelve years in the Guild's cartography corps, charting coastlines and trade routes from the Pale Reach to the Saffron Delta. You've mapped countless leagues, fought off things in uncharted places, and decided that some places should appear on no map. When the Guild needed someone to survey the borderlands, you were the obvious choice. You asked for standard gear, a stipend, papers to requisition gear. They gave you a ring instead. 
  +set_skill combat 4
  +set_skill bushcraft 2
  +set_skill cunning 2
  +set_name "The Cartographer"
  +open Gameplay_Intro
